channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: WATCH: Dramatic Video Shows IDF Demolishing Miles of Terrorist Tunnels in Gaza
Swing state voters say Biden debate performance 'really impactful' on their presidential election decision
item.description: Voters in swing state New Hampshire say President Biden's extremely rough debate performance with Donald Trump will weigh heavily on their decision of whom to support in the 2024 election rematch

item.title: Budget Amendment Aims to End DC Statehood Efforts
item.description: Rep. Andy Ogles, R-Tenn., has introduced an amendment intended to halt efforts toward D.C. statehood, sparking significant backlash from district representatives, The Hill reported.

item.title: AP Nails WH in Head-Spinning Falsehood About Neurologist's Visit
Lawmakers demand answers from top Michigan official over suspected pro-Democrat electioneering
item.description: House Republicans from Michigan demanded documentation from a Michigan official regarding purported weaponization of federal funds for electioneering in the state.

item.title: 16 AGs Petition Supreme Court on Wis. Parents' Rights Case
item.description: Sixteen state attorneys general filed an amicus brief to the U.S. Supreme Court on behalf of a lawsuit in Wisconsin surrounding a school district's policy to exclude parents from discussions with children about changing their gender identity while at school.

item.title: WATCH: Trump Comes Out Swinging, Torches Kamala Harris
NATO summit in DC is 'pivotal' make-or-break for Biden as scrutiny over fitness for office intensifies
item.description: NATO leaders gather in Washington, D.C., this week to discuss Ukraine and other global threats as the war lurches through its third year and President Biden faces scrutiny.

item.title: Stephanopoulos: 'Don't Think Biden Can Serve 4 More Years'
item.description: ABC News anchor George Stephanopoulos, days after his interview with President Joe Biden in prime time, purportedly told a passer-by that he doesn't think he can serve four more years in the White House.

item.title: UPDATED: George Stephanopoulos Says About Biden, 'I Don't Think He Can Serve 4 More Years'
Florida woman charged after allegedly making online death threats toward DeSantis: 'Will not be tolerated'
item.description: A Florida woman was arrested after she allegedly admitted to making "life-threatening statements" against Republican Gov. Ron DeSantis, prompting concerns among his office staff.

item.title: Sen. Ron Johnson to Newsmax: Democrats Face Reality Over Biden's Health Cover-Up
item.description: Sen. Ron Johnson, R-Wis., criticized Democrats for allegedly concealing President Joe Biden's health issues, asserting that their reluctance to address the matter stems from their unrelenting desire to maintain power.

item.title: BREAKING: Trump Challenges Biden to a Debate 'This Week' and to 18 Holes of Golf
Trump wants Biden, hits Kamala, as White House admits visits by Parkinsonâ€™s doctor
item.description: Former President Donald Trump may soon announce his VP choice, as President Joe Biden faces increased calls to step aside amid concerns over his health.

item.title: Sen. Sullivan to Newsmax: Canada Not Paying Its Share to NATO
item.description: Sen. Dan Sullivan, R-Alaska, told Newsmax on Monday he pressed Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau about why his country doesn't pay its fair share as one of 32 members of the military alliance.
